2. I

UB %<>%
  data.frame() %>%                                                      # Data Frame   
  mutate(Personal.Loan = ifelse(Personal.Loan == 1, "yes", "no")) %>%   # Target   
  dplyr::select(-1)                                                     # ID  

# 1. Convert to Factor
UB$Personal.Loan <- factor(UB$Personal.Loan)                            # Target  

# 2. Select Variables used for Analysis
col <- c("Age", "Experience", "Income", "ZIP.Code", "CCAvg", "Mortgage",#   
          "Personal.Loan")                                              # Target
   
UB.df <- UB %>%
  dplyr::select(all_of(col))                                            #     ->

4. 

# Partition (Training Dataset : Test Dataset = 7:3)
y      <- UB.df$Personal.Loan                            # Target

set.seed(200)
ind    <- createDataPartition(y, p = 0.7, list = T)      # Index  7:3 
UB.trd <- UB.df[ind$Resample1,]                          # Training Dataset
UB.ted <- UB.df[-ind$Resample1,]                         # Test Dataset

5. II

# Standardization
preProcValues <- preProcess(UB.trd,
                            method = c("center", "scale"))  # Standardization  -> Training Dataset     

UB.trd <- predict(preProcValues, UB.trd)                    # Standardization for Training Dataset
UB.ted <- predict(preProcValues, UB.ted)                    # Standardization for Test Dataset

7-2-2. ROC 

ac  <- UB.ted$Personal.Loan                             # Test Dataset  class 
pp  <- as.numeric(UB.lda.pred$posterior[,2])            # "Personal.Loan = yes"

1) Package pROC

pacman::p_load("pROC")

lda.roc  <- roc(ac, pp, plot = T, col = "gray")         # roc( class,  )
auc      <- round(auc(lda.roc), 3)
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")

Caution! Package "pROC" ROC .

#  plot.roc() 
plot.roc(lda.roc,   
         col="gray",                                    # Line Color
         print.auc = TRUE,                              # AUC  
         print.auc.col = "red",                         # AUC  
         print.thres = TRUE,                            # Cutoff Value  
         print.thres.pch = 19,                          # Cutoff Value   
         print.thres.col = "red",                       # Cutoff Value   
         auc.polygon = TRUE,                            #     
         auc.polygon.col = "gray90")                    #    

#  ggroc() 
ggroc(lda.roc) +
annotate(geom = "text", x = 0.9, y = 1.0,
label = paste("AUC = ", auc),
size = 5,
color="red") +
theme_bw()

2) Package Epi

pacman::p_load("Epi")       
# install_version("etm", version = "1.1", repos = "http://cran.us.r-project.org")

ROC(pp, ac, plot = "ROC")                                  # ROC( ,  class)

3) Package ROCR

pacman::p_load("ROCR")

lda.pred <- prediction(pp, ac)                             # prediction( ,  class)    

lda.perf <- performance(lda.pred, "tpr", "fpr")            # performance(, "", "1-")                      
plot(lda.perf, col = "gray")                               # ROC Curve

perf.auc   <- performance(lda.pred, "auc")                 # AUC
auc        <- attributes(perf.auc)$y.values 
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")
